@page "/services"
@using PureWave.Web.Data

<PageTitle>PureWave | Services</PageTitle>

<section class="page-intro">
    <span class="section-tag">Services</span>
    <h1>Smart home automation and media systems that make your space work the way you want it to.</h1>
    <p>
        Beyond acoustic design and calibration, PureWave helps clients build intelligent spaces — rooms that respond to what you're doing,
        libraries that manage themselves, and systems that remove friction from how you watch and listen.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section-band">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-tag">Smart Home</span>
        <h2>Take control of your space with Home Assistant.</h2>
    </div>

    <img src="/images/services-smarthome.jpg"
         alt="Smart home control via smartphone app"
         style="width:100%;border-radius:22px;display:block;margin-bottom:1.5rem;" />

    <p>
        Home Assistant is an open-source home automation platform that runs locally on your network — no cloud subscription,
        no data leaving your home, no dependency on a third-party service staying alive. It connects your lights, climate system,
        AV equipment, and sensors into a single dashboard you control from your phone, a tablet, or a wall panel.
    </p>

    <div class="process-grid" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Movie Mode</h3>
            <p>One tap dims the lights to cinema level, fires up the projector, closes the blinds, and adjusts the climate — all before the opening credits roll.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Intelligent Sensors</h3>
            <p>Zigbee and ESP sensors detect presence, measure ambient light, and monitor air quality — the room adjusts automatically without you touching anything.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>One Dashboard</h3>
            <p>Replace the multi-remote clutter with a single interface. Scenes, schedules, and automations all live in one place, accessible from anywhere on your network.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-band">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-tag">Media Automation</span>
        <h2>Your own private streaming platform — no subscriptions, no disappearing content.</h2>
    </div>

    <img src="/images/services-cinema.jpg"
         alt="Home cinema seating"
         style="width:100%;border-radius:22px;display:block;margin-bottom:1.5rem;" />

    <p>
        Streaming services raise prices, remove titles, and split libraries across multiple platforms. Media automation gives you a self-managed
        alternative: a personal library with a Netflix-quality interface, true 4K HDR quality, and content available on every screen in your home
        — with no monthly fee once it's running.
    </p>

    <div class="process-grid" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Plex</h3>
            <p>The front end — displays your library with posters, metadata, and trailers. Tracks watch history and resumes across every device you own.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Sonarr</h3>
            <p>TV automation — monitors for new episodes and downloads them automatically in the highest available quality the moment they're released.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Radarr</h3>
            <p>Movie automation — grabs films as soon as they become available in your preferred format, from 1080p to full 4K HDR.</p>
        </article>
    </div>

    <div class="section-block">
        <h3>How it works end to end</h3>
        <p>
            You request a title. The system searches for the best available version, downloads and processes it automatically,
            and Plex notifies you when it's ready to watch. No manual file management, no waiting for someone else's release schedule.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-band" style="text-align:center;">
    <span class="section-tag">Get Started</span>
    <h2>Interested in smart home setup or building a media system?</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Start with a WhatsApp message — describe what you want your space to do and PureWave will talk you through the options.
    </p>
    <a class="button-primary"
       href="@SiteConfig.WhatsAppOnSiteUrl"
       target="_blank"
       rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <WhatsAppIcon /> Ask about smart home setup
    </a>
</section>
